Iranian President: If Sanctions on Iran are Lifted, Nuclear Agreement Negotiations are Likely to Reach an Agreement - Xinhua News
"Tehran, December 11 (Reporters Gao Wencheng, Wang Shoubao) Iranian President Hassan Rouhani said on the 11th in the Iranian capital Tehran that if the United States lifts sanctions on Iran, a comprehensive nuclear agreement can be reached with Iran."
According to a message published on the website of the Iranian President, Rouhani said during a meeting with ambassadors from Iran's neighboring countries that by submitting proposals to the other parties involved in the Iran nuclear agreement, Iran has demonstrated its sincerity in negotiations.
"If the US shows determination, the road to reaching an agreement will be clear."
The parties involved in the Iran nuclear agreement began talks in Vienna, the capital of Austria, in April of this year to discuss the issue of the US and Iran returning to compliance.
A new round of talks started on November 29th in Vienna and were temporarily adjourned on December 3rd, and resumed on the 9th.